ted Aircraft fell\nwell over a point.\nLukens Steel recovered about\na point of its 10-point low of\nyesterday. Youngstown Sheet\ndropped 2 points. United States\nSteel and Republic Steel each\nlost a point or to and Bethle\nhem a fraction.\nGulf Oil fell well over 2\npoints. Most other of the lead\ning oils clung narrowly to the\nupside, but Standard Oil 'New\nJersey* eased.\ni Corporate bonds rose. Oov-\nS ernment bonds edged higher.\nN. Y. PROPUCE\n_ NEW YORK. \u00abr> IUBDA.\nRutter about atrat|T fataipta SltM.lltU) i\nWhole,ale nrlcea on bulk carton,\n(freak* Creamer*. 09 score (AAI (it- 1\nAl'y rent,, ,<#r* fA.\nIHi .core t\u00df> A-:-0-:3w.\nChee\u00bbe gteady, Receipt, S\u2019B.OOO\nertcc* unchanged.\nWhole,ale rgXJ\u00dftbu steady. Ke\neatota ltL-ifO NeA Turg \u00ab\u00bbt ouo\ntatiooa faOaw Mldwoatern niiaed\ncolors: extras ISA-Stl Ibg l\nextras bra* t\u00ab.v\u00ab* lb* M-64 e\u00bb-\ntra, medium Uo<t2- aasallti \u2022.'S-\u2019.\u2019H.\n\u2022tandarda Krai AIMS: check. ni-Ht\nWhite.! eitraa (At-SO Sri\nextra* la it* (4 VAA the) AT-10. ei\ntraa medium mE Brawnal aatraa\n(48-SA In.i AA-SB\nNearby: wMtet: too oualttv (4\u00bb-V.\nlbs OH-iM; medlna, 4i-\u00bb33>: email, 1\npeeweew lI*ST Browna\ntoo quality n*-S\u00ab Ib, i SB-81 modi\numa to',-41. imalla Sl-\u00dcb: peeuee,\nSl-2S.\nNEW YORK COTTON\n\u2014W. aiMH\nW\nUtah Low Ml c*T\nGoOllf AIT 4* 30 ATM ABM AO -t\n\u25a0loPort*. \u00bb0 70 a 2* B* \u2014J*\nLlnTanaOrt 0 27M 27% 27%. t*\nINd.irtJ*a\u00aba IB 23m T\u00bbb 2Ww-\n,'toa.rre.oj SB *o'* BB>* BBM-\nL'tdAiltWof* Li H RS 07 -7*.\nCtdArttW IMr T IBM IB IB Mfi*\nLUd Carkoa t B 3 SOM MRS\u2014 M\nto* .no 24a Ml o*k AM W*- M\nL'UtTMoAThm IA Bb Mb V*- H\nrtdETo.il as 4 093* SBM SBM\nLm4 EnaAE 1 A LA IBM >1330\nthd Fruit BO ASM 42 42 3*\nUtdOaaCom IA JOM JOM 5034-'M\nrtdPkCMina A IM JM lM\nCtdMMSMh A ST SOM SO%-\nrS\u00dforai 39 AB ABM 44 M\nL SAEort tS* 10 JOM 3034 M* M\nLBGyvsum Sa IS OOM 4l>* OIM-lM\nIWRatrMrta SB T 7\nV S Induat I IB IBM ISM 123*- U\n